The paper deals with the combinatorial properties of reversible cellular automata, which are closely related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the decomposition of reversible CA into block permutations, which is a topic in combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also mentions quantum computing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper provides upper bounds on the block neighborhood, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.LO).
